description.narrative: UNICEF health staff efficiently and effectively contributed to health programming and monitored effectively to achieve planned results. All planned activities were on track, with 100 per cent utilization of allocated funds, no over-six or over-nine-month DCT, 100 per cent HACT assurance, monitoring visits, spot checks, and donor report submission. 95 per cent of staff participated in a health staff retreat and were informed on the ITF report. Technical assistance, coordination and collaboration with government and partners propagated UNICEF's agenda for health sector reform, in line with the Health Strategy, Country Programme, Post- Astana Declaration on primary healthcare and national priorities | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
